                Header = "How We Handle Your Data";
                Body = $@"
Collected Data

The application stores exclusively technically necessary information, including:
- Hashed username and password (Argon2) in the local or cloud database
- Language setting
- Last login date/time
- Authentication information in the form of encrypted cookies (only technically necessary cookies)
- Storage location preference (local / cloud / both)
- Text direction (LTR/RTL)
- Accessibility settings
- Design/theme mode
- Identity provider information (Microsoft, Google, Apple) solely for authentication purposes

Optional Debug ID

Users may voluntarily enter a temporary debug ID to better analyze their own issues. This debug ID:
- is not automatically generated
- is not stored permanently
- is not linked to a user account
- can be deleted or changed at any time

Data Anonymization

To maximize the protection of your privacy, we apply the following measures:
- All login credentials are stored exclusively in hashed form and cannot be associated with any natural person without additional information.
- We do not store any personally identifiable information (PII).
- Users are themselves responsible for any personal content they voluntarily store in the app. This data is not processed, analyzed, or read by True Perfect Code.

Note:
- If users actively contact us and voluntarily provide their debug identifier, we may temporarily use it for error analysis. After completion of the support request, no connection is retained.

Purpose of Data Collection

Your data is processed only to the extent strictly necessary for the operation of the app:
- Ensuring the functionality and provision of the application.
- Legal basis pursuant to Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (EU General Data Protection Regulation) for the use of app features.
- Technically necessary cookies and settings are additionally based on Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in a secure and functional app).

Data Storage Location

Your data is hosted under strict security standards and in compliance with European data protection principles:
- When using cloud storage, data is stored encrypted on servers in Switzerland operated by Firestorm (a reputable Swiss hosting provider).

Data Sharing with Third Parties

Your privacy is our top priority, therefore:
- No data is shared with third parties.
- No tracking or analytics services are used.

User Rights

Users can at any time:
- delete local data, cloud data, or both
- view or export all their stored data in the app
- completely delete their user account

Note:
- Since no personally identifiable information is collected, True Perfect Code cannot assign or provide user-specific data externally, unless the user voluntarily shares a debug ID for support purposes.

Data Protection Officer
- Daniel S. Simic, Dipl. Techniker HF Informatik
- Contact: privacy@true-perfect-code.ch
";
